      <h3>Intro</h3>
      <p>
        An asset based loan is when a business puts up something valuable as security on a loan.  If a business can't pay back the loan, the bank takes the asset instead. A business puts up stuff it owns like its inventory, equipment, debts or machinery. Business banks, and other certified lenders, prefer assets which, in the event of a delinquent loan, that they can easily sell to recover the unpaid debt.  Asset based loans are good for businesses that have a business growth strategy of owning hard assets like construction, retail, and manufacturing. 
      </p>
      <blockquote>
        <p>The SBA offers aid, advice, assistance and protects the interests of small businesses.</p>
